  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package contains a subtle consistency weakness: one validation result carries an evidenceTimestamp that falls approximately 47 minutes after the package signatureTimestamp, consistent with a race-condition artifact in automated evidence ingestion pipelines.",
